This project contains implementation for 4 algorithms: Merge, Quick, Heap, and Shaker sort. It contains a testing client with methods for generating and printing data after being operated on by each algorithm, and a Result class for holding the sorted integer lists and total number of comparisons made by each algorithm. Method generateData() creates the specified number of integer lists of size n = 4, 6, or 8. Each algorithm method accepts an integer list as input and returns the sorted integer list and number of comparisons packaged together within a Result object, which is then printed with the printData() method. The testing client contains an equal number of tests for each list size to measure the algorithmic efficiency on integer lists with variable size. Most of the algorithms use helper methods for recursive calls, such as the mergeHelper() method in the MergeSort class, which reports back to the central mergeSort() method which is referenced in the testing client.
This project was created using the Eclipse IDE, with the execution environment version JavaSE-11.
